The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 11 November is 7,121 (824.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 06 November, there were 857 new confirmed cases (99.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 October, there were 839 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 2% ( 18 extra cases).
